name: r-bfa
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.4' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-bfa
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/bfa_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/bfa/bfa_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 66e4efbc87cb5f565e5f791bdeb323e45c962e14db44ac33f8880bda0d21c622

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1003

  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}      # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp >=0.10.6
    - r-rcpparmadillo
    - r-coda

  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp >=0.10.6
    - r-rcpparmadillo
    - r-coda

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('bfa')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('bfa')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=bfa
  license: GPL-3
  summary: Provides model fitting for several Bayesian factor models including Gaussian, ordinal
    probit, mixed and semiparametric Gaussian copula factor models under a range of
    priors.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
